### Basic example
Use the `Dialog`, `Dialog:Title`, `Dialog:Description`, `Dialog:Body`, and `Dialog:Actions` components to build a dialog:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Basic example', {height: '400px'}) }}

### Dialog width
Use the `size` prop on the `Dialog` component to control the max-width of the dialog:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Dialog width', {height: '400px'}) }}
Available size options include `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl`, `3xl`, `4xl`, and `5xl`.

### Opening from dropdown
When opening a `Dialog` from a dropdown menu, make sure the dialog is rendered outside of the dropdown:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Opening from dropdown', {height: '400px'}) }}
If your `Dialog` is placed inside the dropdown, it won't open as expected because it will be immediately unmounted when the dropdown menu closes.

### Auto-focusing elements
Add the `autofocus` attribute to any form control or button in the dialog to automatically focus it when the dialog opens:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Auto-focusing elements', {height: '400px'}) }}

### With scrolling content
Dialogs automatically become scrollable if their content is taller than the viewport:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'With scrolling content', {height: '300px'}) }}
